Hotel Bookings — Business Insights & Glossary

Project: Test_HotelBookings

Business Domain: Hotel Bookings Management — City & Resort Hotels (Portugal)

Data window: July 2015 – August 2017

Documented: 2026-06-19



Part 1 — Business Overview

The dataset covers two hotels — a City Hotel and a Resort Hotel — located in Portugal. Together they process bookings from guests originating in 178 countries across all 7 continents, with Europe accounting for the overwhelming majority of demand.


Business Model
• Inbound hospitality — primarily serves international leisure and business travellers arriving in Portugal
• Dual-property — two hotels with distinct profiles: City Hotel targets shorter urban stays at higher rates; Resort Hotel caters to longer leisure stays
• OTA-dependent — 68% of bookings flow through Online or Offline Travel Agencies
• High-cancellation environment — overall cancellation rate of 37.58%, well above the hospitality industry benchmark of 20–30%
• Primarily European demand — Portugal, UK, France, Spain, and Germany account for the majority of bookings and revenue

