Insight 6: Non-Refundable Deposits Show a 99.36% Cancellation Rate — A Revenue Recognition Gap

Deposit Type	Bookings	Canceled	Cancel Rate	Revenue Recorded
Non Refund	14,586	14,493	99.36%	$17,110
No Deposit	102,828	29,659	28.84%	$25,940,879
Refundable	162	36	22.22%	$28,987

When a Non Refund booking is canceled, estimated_revenue is set to $0 by design. However, a Non Refund booking means the hotel keeps the deposit regardless of cancellation. The mart therefore records $0 for bookings where actual cash was collected.


Business implication: The $25,986,976 total estimated_revenue understates true hotel revenue by the full value of deposits kept on Non Refund cancellations. If actual P&L reporting is required, revenue from non-refundable cancellations must be captured separately in the mart layer.



Insight 7: ADR Has Grown 29% Across the Data Window — With a Consistent Summer Peak

