Transient guests (75.1% of bookings) cancel at 41.34%, pulling the blended rate above 37%. Group bookings (0.5% of volume) cancel at only 8.74% — the lowest of any customer type. Contract customers stay the longest (5.34 nights) and represent a reliable extended-stay segment.


Business implication: Contract and Group customers are disproportionately valuable per booking — they stay longer (Contract) or almost never cancel (Group). Growing direct corporate partnerships and group event business is a structurally higher-quality revenue strategy than growing Transient OTA volume.



Part 3 — Business Glossary

A

ADR — Average Daily Rate

The average revenue earned per occupied room per night, before adjustment for cancellations.

• Formula: AVG(adr) from fct_bookings
• Column: fct_bookings.adr (decimal(10,2))
• Benchmark: $103.34 overall | City Hotel $106.74 | Resort Hotel $96.59
• Note: 178 bookings have adr = 0 (complimentary stays). Exclude with WHERE adr > 0 for rate-only analysis.

ADR Adjusted

ADR recalculated with canceled bookings set to $0; reflects only confirmed revenue-generating stays.

• Formula: CASE WHEN is_canceled = false THEN adr ELSE 0 END
• Column: fct_bookings.adr_adjusted
• Benchmark: $63.91 overall | City Hotel $62.49 | Resort Hotel $66.72
• Note: The gap between ADR and ADR Adjusted measures the per-room dollar cost of cancellations. City Hotel gap ($44.25) is materially larger than Resort Hotel ($29.88).

Arrival Date Key

Integer surrogate key in YYYYMMDD format linking fct_bookings to dim_arrival_date.

• Column: fct_bookings.arrival_date_key (int)
• Example: 20160715 = July 15, 2016
• Note: Constructed in staging from three separate source columns: arrival_date_year, arrival_date_month, arrival_date_day_of_month.

Assigned Room Type

The room type code actually given to the guest at check-in — may differ from the reserved room type.

• Column: fct_bookings.assigned_room_key FK to dim_assigned_room
• Note: dim_assigned_room contains 12 room type codes vs dim_reserved_room's 10 — 2 assigned types have never appeared as reserved room types.


B

Babies

Number of infants (typically under 2 years old) in the booking party. Sub-component of total_guests.

• Column: fct_bookings.babies (int)

Bed and Breakfast (BB)

The most common meal plan — accommodation plus breakfast only. Represents 77.36% of all bookings.

• Column: dim_booking_attributes.meal = 'BB', meal_name = 'Bed & Breakfast'
• Avg ADR: $100.83 | Cancel Rate: 37.93%

Booking Changes

Number of modifications made to the booking after initial confirmation (date, room type, guest count, etc.).

• Column: fct_bookings.booking_changes (tinyint)
• Note: Higher change counts may correlate with lower cancellation risk — an actively engaged guest is more likely to complete their stay.

Booking Key

Surrogate primary key for fct_bookings. Auto-generated bigint with no business meaning.

• Column: fct_bookings.booking_key (bigint)
• Use: COUNT(booking_key) for total booking volume.


C

Cancellation Rate

The proportion of total bookings that were canceled.

• Formula: SUM(is_canceled_float) / COUNT(booking_key) x 100
• Benchmark: 37.58% overall — well above the industry norm of 20-30%
• By hotel: City Hotel 42.30% | Resort Hotel 28.21%
• By segment: Groups 61.77% | Online TA 36.96% | Corporate 19.00% | Direct 15.57%

Children

Number of children (typically 2-12 years) in the booking party. Sub-component of total_guests.

• Column: fct_bookings.children (int)

City Hotel

The larger of the two hotels. Urban setting; shorter average stays (2.99 nights); higher raw ADR ($106.74); higher cancellation rate (42.30%). Represents 66.5% of all bookings and 55.4% of estimated revenue.

• Dim reference: dim_hotels.hotel_name = 'City Hotel', hotel_type = 'City'

Complementary

A market segment for complimentary (free) stays — ADR averages $14.59 and cancel rate is 60.54%. Only 147 bookings. Exclude from rate and revenue analyses.


Contract

Customer type for guests on fixed recurring agreements (corporate accounts, extended partnerships). 4,053 bookings (3.4%), averaging 5.34 nights — the longest stay profile of any customer type.

• Column: dim_booking_attributes.customer_type = 'Contract'

Country Key

Foreign key in fct_bookings linking to dim_country.

• Column: fct_bookings.country_key (bigint) FK to dim_country.country_key
• Coverage: 178 countries. Includes continent = 'Unknown' and continent = 'Antarctica' — treat as data quality issues; exclude from geographic analysis.


D

Days in Waiting List

Number of days the booking spent on a waiting list before being confirmed.

• Column: fct_bookings.days_in_waiting_list (int)
• Benchmark: Most bookings = 0 (direct confirmation). Non-zero values are a demand pressure signal useful for identifying peak dates where yield management is most critical.

Deposit Type

The type of upfront payment required at the time of booking.

• Column: dim_booking_attributes.deposit_type
• Values:
- No Deposit — 102,828 bookings (87.5%), 28.84% cancel rate

- Non Refund — 14,586 bookings (12.4%), 99.36% cancel rate — see Insight 6

- Refundable — 162 bookings (0.1%), 22.22% cancel rate

• Critical note: Revenue from kept non-refundable deposits on canceled bookings is NOT captured in estimated_revenue.

Distribution Channel

How the booking physically reached the hotel's reservation system.

• Column: dim_booking_attributes.distribution_channel
• Values: TA/TO · Direct · Corporate · GDS · Unknown
• Note: Distinct from market_segment — e.g. an Online TA booking may arrive via the TA/TO distribution channel.


E

Estimated Revenue

Projected revenue from a booking based on rate and stay duration. Set to $0 for all canceled bookings.

• Formula: adr x total_nights when is_canceled = false; else $0
• Column: fct_bookings.estimated_revenue (decimal(12,2))
• Total (dataset): $25,986,976
• Note: Does NOT include revenue from kept non-refundable deposits. Does NOT reflect final invoiced amounts.


F

fct_bookings

The central fact table of the hotel bookings mart. One row per booking.

• Grain: One row per booking
• Rows: 117,576 (filtered from 119,390 source rows; 1,814 invalid bookings excluded via is_valid_booking = false)
• Surrogate key: booking_key (bigint)
• Source: int_bookings_flagged WHERE is_valid_booking = true

Full Board (FB)

Meal plan covering all meals (breakfast, lunch, dinner). Highest cancellation rate of any meal plan at 61.05% despite commanding a $111.13 ADR.

• Column: dim_booking_attributes.meal = 'FB'
• Bookings: 783 (0.67% share)


G

Group

Customer type for formal group bookings (tour groups, event attendees). Only 549 bookings (0.47% of total) but the lowest cancellation rate of any customer type at 8.74%.

• Column: dim_booking_attributes.customer_type = 'Group'
• Note: Do not confuse with the Groups market segment (61.77% cancel rate). These are separate dimensions that behave very differently.


H

Half Board (HB)

Meal plan including accommodation, breakfast, and dinner. Second most popular at 12.14% share. Commands the highest ADR of any meal type at $121.87 — a 21% premium over Bed and Breakfast.

• Column: dim_booking_attributes.meal = 'HB'
• Cancel rate: 34.88% — slightly below the overall average.

Historical Cancellation Rate

Guest-level risk indicator: the proportion of a guest's prior bookings that were canceled before the current booking was made.

• Formula: previous_cancellations / (previous_cancellations + previous_bookings_not_canceled)
• Column: fct_bookings.historical_cancellation_rate (decimal(5,4))
• Range: 0.0 to 1.0
• Critical note: NULL for 92.2% of rows (108,384 bookings) — first-time guests with no prior history. Always filter WHERE historical_cancellation_rate IS NOT NULL before aggregating. Among non-NULL rows the average is approximately 0.65.

Hotel Key

Foreign key in fct_bookings linking to dim_hotels.

• Column: fct_bookings.hotel_key (bigint)


I

is_canceled

Boolean flag indicating whether the booking was canceled.

• Column: fct_bookings.is_canceled (bit); true (1) = canceled, false (0) = confirmed
• Companion: is_canceled_float (float) for aggregation — SUM(is_canceled_float) = count of cancellations
• Effect: Sets adr_adjusted and estimated_revenue to $0 for all canceled rows.

is_repeated_guest

Boolean flag — true when the guest had at least one prior confirmed booking at the same hotel.

• Column: fct_bookings.is_repeated_guest (bit); companion: is_repeated_guest_int (int)
• Benchmark: Only 3,292 bookings (2.80%) are from repeated guests — an extremely low loyalty rate.

is_room_type_changed

Boolean flag — true when assigned_room_type differs from reserved_room_type at check-in.

• Column: fct_bookings.is_room_type_changed (bit); companion: is_room_type_changed_int (int)
• Benchmark: 14,113 bookings (12.00%) had a room change. Room Type A has the highest change rate at 13.93%.

is_weekend

Derived boolean in dim_arrival_date. 1 = guest arrives Saturday or Sunday; 0 = weekday arrival.

• Column: dim_arrival_date.is_weekend (bit)
• Benchmark: 31,838 weekend arrivals (27.1%) vs 85,738 weekday (72.9%). Weekend arrivals have marginally higher ADR ($104.24 vs $103.01) and lower cancel rate (36.7% vs 37.91%).


L

Lead Time

Number of days between the booking date and the scheduled arrival date.

• Column: fct_bookings.lead_time (smallint)
• Range: 0 (same-day) to 737 days | Benchmark: 105 days average
• Critical insight: Strongest single predictor of cancellation risk — from 7.19% (same-day) to 68% (365+ days). See Insight 2.

Length of Stay (Total Nights)

Total nights in the stay = weekend nights + weekday nights.

• Formula: stays_in_weekend_nights + stays_in_week_nights
• Column: fct_bookings.total_nights (tinyint)
• Benchmark: 3.45 nights average | City Hotel 2.99 | Resort Hotel 4.37 | Contract customers 5.34
• Note: 23 bookings have total_nights = 0 (same-day / day-use). Exclude with WHERE total_nights > 0 for LOS analysis.


M

Market Segment

The commercial channel category through which the booking originated.

• Column: dim_booking_attributes.market_segment
• Values: Online TA · Offline TA/TO · Groups · Direct · Corporate · Complementary · Aviation
• Benchmark: Online TA = 47.7% of all bookings. Direct = lowest cancel rate (15.57%) with equivalent ADR to Online TA.

Meal Plan

The food and beverage package bundled with the room rate.

• Columns: dim_booking_attributes.meal (code) · dim_booking_attributes.meal_name (full name)
• Values: BB (Bed and Breakfast) · HB (Half Board) · SC (Self Catering) · FB (Full Board) · None


N

No Deposit

Booking made without any upfront payment. Most common deposit type — 102,828 bookings (87.5% of total). Cancel rate: 28.84%.


Non Refund

Booking where a non-refundable deposit was collected. 14,586 bookings (12.4%). Cancel rate: 99.36%. Revenue from kept deposits is not captured in estimated_revenue — see Insight 6.



P

Party Size (Total Guests)

Total number of people in the booking: adults + children + babies.

• Formula: adults + children + babies
• Column: fct_bookings.total_guests (int)
• Benchmark: 1.97 average | Weekend arrivals 2.05 | Weekday arrivals 1.94

Previous Bookings Not Canceled

Count of the guest's prior confirmed bookings at the same hotel before the current booking.

• Column: fct_bookings.previous_bookings_not_canceled (tinyint)
• Use: Denominator component of historical_cancellation_rate.

Previous Cancellations

Count of the guest's prior canceled bookings at the same hotel before the current booking.

• Column: fct_bookings.previous_cancellations (tinyint)
• Use: Numerator of historical_cancellation_rate.


R

Refundable

Deposit type where a deposit was paid but returned to the guest on cancellation. Only 162 bookings (0.1%), cancel rate 22.22%.


Repeated Guest

A guest who has made at least one prior confirmed stay at the same hotel.

• Flag: fct_bookings.is_repeated_guest = true
• Benchmark: Only 3,292 bookings (2.80%) — well below typical hospitality loyalty benchmarks.

Required Car Parking Spaces

Number of parking spaces requested by the guest.

• Column: fct_bookings.required_car_parking_spaces (tinyint)
• Use: Operational capacity planning; useful as a segmentation indicator.

Reserved Room Type

The room type originally requested by the guest at booking time.

• Column: fct_bookings.reserved_room_key FK to dim_reserved_room
• Values: Room types A through P (10 types). Room A = 72% of all bookings.
• Note: Room type P is present in dim_reserved_room but has zero bookings in fct_bookings.

Resort Hotel

The smaller, leisure-focused hotel. Longer average stays (4.37 nights); lower ADR ($96.59); lower cancellation rate (28.21%). Represents 33.5% of bookings and 44.6% of estimated revenue.

• Dim reference: dim_hotels.hotel_name = 'Resort Hotel', hotel_type = 'Resort'


S

Self Catering (SC)

Meal plan with no included meals — guests prepare their own food or dine out. 10,428 bookings (8.87%). Cancel rate 37.84%.

• Column: dim_booking_attributes.meal = 'SC'

Special Requests

Number of specific requests submitted by the guest at booking (e.g. high floor, twin beds, non-smoking room).

• Column: fct_bookings.total_of_special_requests (tinyint)
• Benchmark: 0.57 average per booking | Weekend arrivals 0.62 | Weekday arrivals 0.55

Status Date Key

Integer surrogate key in YYYYMMDD format linking fct_bookings to dim_status_date. Represents the date of the last booking status change (check-out or cancellation date).

• Column: fct_bookings.status_date_key FK to dim_status_date
• Note: reservation_status (Check-Out / Canceled / No-Show) is NOT carried to the mart — only the status date is joinable. Add reservation_status to fct_bookings in CODE mode if granular status reporting is required.

Stays in Week Nights

Number of weekday nights (Monday-Friday) in the booking. Component of total_nights.

• Column: fct_bookings.stays_in_week_nights (tinyint)

Stays in Weekend Nights

Number of weekend nights (Saturday-Sunday) in the booking. Component of total_nights.

• Column: fct_bookings.stays_in_weekend_nights (tinyint)

